race.comment: KAYE JAY (6) ran a strong race on debut at Cranbourne over 1400m, getting home well to be beaten under a length in second. He should relish the rise to 1600m now and while the draw isn't ideal, his natural upside should see him very hard to hold out. NIGHTOWL (1) makes his Australian debut. He was knocking on the door in New Zealand prior to a let-up, finishing second in his past three outings. Have to respect him. MIKE'S HOPE (7) was well backed on debut at Cranbourne, sent out as a $3.40 chance and battled on fairly well for third. He should be better for that and Lane goes aboard now. TRYST AND DOUBT (9) stuck on well on debut at Geelong when beaten narrowly into third. Up in trip looks okay, he should in this for a long way. KIRKHOEPASSE (13) ran a solid race on debut at Cranbourne and should progress.
